GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  The full feedback row { feedbackId, kind, scope, status, description, command, errorText, cliVersion, context, resolution, createdAt, ... }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Permission denied      → requires a developer token
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  Not found              → check the id via \`ib dev feedback list\`. Not there? A user-filed tracked bug lives in the SEPARATE bugReport system — try \`ib dev bug get <id>\` or \`ib dev bug list\`.
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

SEE ALSO
