`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib dev feedback list matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib dev feedback list [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  List filed feedback for triage. Developer-only (isSystemAdmin / isDeveloper). Newest first, paginated (default 50, cap 200). By DEFAULT returns only active items (status open + reviewed) — closed items (applied/dismissed) are hidden; pass --all for every status, or --status to name specific ones.
  Permissions: requires isSystemAdmin or isDeveloper.

FLAGS
  --status STRING    open | reviewed | applied | dismissed, or a comma-separated list (e.g. open,reviewed)
  --unresolved BOOLEAN    Shortcut for --status open,reviewed (un-closed items) — same as the default; mutually exclusive with --status/--all
  --all BOOLEAN    Include every status (open,reviewed,applied,dismissed); overrides the open+reviewed default; mutually exclusive with --status/--unresolved
  --kind STRING    improvement | bug | idea | legal
  --scope STRING    cli | app | jerry | bsg2 | workspace | other
  --search STRING    Substring match over description/command/resolution/errorText (deploy-gated)
  --limit NUMBER    Max rows (cap 200) (default: 50)
  --offset NUMBER    Pagination offset (default: 0)
  --full BOOLEAN    Return untruncated description/resolution (default: each capped at 200 chars)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { items: FeedbackRow[] (description/resolution/errorText capped at 200 chars unless --full), nextCursor: null, count, truncated?, hint? }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 4  Validation             → use only one of --all / --unresolved / --status; --status values must be open|reviewed|applied|dismissed
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Permission denied      → requires a developer token (isSystemAdmin/isDeveloper)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - Default scope is the active bucket (open + reviewed). Pass --all to include closed (applied/dismissed) items, or --status applied to target them.
  - --search is a server-side substring filter added in a later backend version; against an older backend it is silently ignored (the list returns unfiltered) — deploy-gated.

EXAMPLES
  ib dev feedback list
  ib dev feedback list --all
  ib dev feedback list --status applied --scope cli
  ib dev feedback list --kind bug --limit 20
  ib dev feedback list --search IDOR
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib dev feedback resolve matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib dev feedback resolve <id> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Triage a feedback row: set its status and/or attach a resolution note (developer-only). This IS a real write — blocked under --read-only (exit 3). --dry-run previews the update body client-side without sending.
  Permissions: requires isSystemAdmin or isDeveloper.

ARGUMENTS
  <id> NUMBER    feedbackId (required)

FLAGS
  --status STRING    open | reviewed | applied | dismissed
  --note STRING    Resolution note stored on the row
  --dry-run BOOLEAN    Print the update body without sending (client-side)
  --full BOOLEAN    Return the full updated row instead of the compact ack

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  A compact ack { feedbackId, status, updatedAt, resolution } (resolution capped at 200 chars; the full row with --full). With --dry-run: { dryRun:true, wouldSend:{ method, path, body } }.

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 4  Validation             → provide --status and/or --note; status must be a known value
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Permission denied      → requires a developer token; also refused under --read-only
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  Not found              → check the id via \`ib dev feedback list\`
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

EXAMPLES
  ib dev feedback resolve 42 --status applied --note "added row counts in CLI v1.3"
  ib dev feedback resolve 42 --status dismissed --note "by design"
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib dev inbox matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib dev inbox [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Aggregated operator inbox: counts of every open/incomplete signal (deploy-pending changelog, unresolved feedback, new bugs, open support, staged legal drafts, glossary misses, live no_supply tarjouspyynnot) plus a memory-groom signal and a \`needsYou\` headline
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

FLAGS
  --details BOOLEAN    Include slimmed top-items per signal, not just counts

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { generatedAt, needsYou, changelog:{ pending, deployPending, maxBumpLevel }, feedback:{ open, reviewed, byKind:{ open, reviewed } }, bugs:{ new }, support:{ open, truncated }, legal:{ drafts }, glossary:{ misses }, jerry:{ noSupplyLive, noSupplyExpired }, memory:{ feedbackId, entryCount, flaggedForRetire, groomDate, daysSince } | null } — with --details each signal also carries an \`items\` array (feedback.items splits into { open, reviewed }; each reviewed item also carries { readyToClose, activeVersion, activatedAt }; jerry.items carry an \`expired\` flag).

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Developer access required → inbox is developer-gated; use a developer/sysadmin token
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - Deploy-gated: 404 until the backend ships GET /api/cli/inbox.

EXAMPLES
  ib dev inbox
  ib dev inbox --details
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib dev perf clear matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib dev perf clear [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Clear the slow-query buffer for one environment. Previews with --dry-run (client-side); --reason recommended for the audit log. Developer-only; refused under --read-only.
  Permissions: requires isSystemAdmin or isDeveloper.

FLAGS
  --env STRING    Environment buffer to clear (default: backend's current env)

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  execute: { cleared:true, environment, message } | --dry-run: { dryRun:true, wouldClear:{ method, path } }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not a developer        → requires isSystemAdmin or isDeveloper
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose
  exit 3  Blocked by read-only mode → clearing needs a session without --read-only/IB_READ_ONLY

NOTES
  - The DELETE route honours no server-side X-Dry-Run — --dry-run is resolved CLIENT-SIDE (never sends).

SEE ALSO
  ib dev perf stats

EXAMPLES
  ib dev perf clear --env staging --reason "reset after load test"
  ib dev perf clear --dry-run
"
`;

