`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib glossary set matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib glossary set <term> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Create/update a glossary entry (developer only). PARTIAL update: only the fields you pass change — omit a flag to KEEP its current value, pass an empty value to CLEAR it. Auto-resolves a matching miss.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <term> STRING    Canonical term (required)

FLAGS
  --definition STRING    One-paragraph definition (≤2000). Omit to keep current.
  --synonyms STRING    Comma-separated aliases incl. inflections. Omit to keep; pass "" to clear.
  --related STRING    Comma-separated command paths, e.g. "ib person,ib vehicle driver board". Omit to keep; pass "" to clear.
  --entity STRING    Related DB entity, e.g. Person / personId. Omit to keep.
  --domain STRING    Domain grouping (e.g. vacation). Omit to keep.
  --update-only BOOLEAN    Only update an existing term; do not create a new one (404 if absent)
  --from-json STRING    Read fields from a JSON object file (or - for stdin); flags override. Only keys present in the object are written (others kept).
  --add-synonyms STRING    Comma-separated synonyms to ADD to the existing list — no full resend. Excl. --synonyms.
  --remove-synonyms STRING    Comma-separated synonyms to REMOVE by name (idempotent). Excl. --synonyms.
  --append-definition STRING    Append a clause to the current definition (single-space join; re-appending identical text is a no-op). Excl. --definition.
  --ai-confidence NUMBER    Self-assessed completeness/correctness 0–100 (groom rubric). Omit on a human edit to reset the score.
  --needs-human-review BOOLEAN    Park the term for a human (excludes it from --needs-review); set with a low --ai-confidence when blocked.

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { term, synonyms, definition, relatedCommands, relatedEntity, domain, runs }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not a developer        → Developer access required
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  Term not found (with --update-only) → Omit --update-only to create the entry
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  append/add/remove on a non-existent term → Create the term first (set --definition …); append requires an existing entry
  exit 4 (HTTP 422)  definition >2000 chars → Shorten the definition
  exit 4  --from-json file is not valid JSON or not readable → Check the file path and contents

NOTES
  - PARTIAL (PATCH) semantics: an omitted flag is NOT sent, so the backend preserves the existing value — you can update just one field (e.g. only --synonyms) without re-sending the definition. To CLEAR a field pass an empty value: \`--synonyms ""\` empties the list, \`--entity ""\` blanks it. To OVERWRITE, pass the new value.
  - Requires the partial-aware backend (COALESCE save proc) deployed; against an older backend an omitted field is still overwritten to empty/null — re-send all fields (or use --from-json) until the backend is updated.
  - Append mode (--add-synonyms / --remove-synonyms / --append-definition) edits in place without re-sending the whole field — built for no-filesystem callers (MCP ib_exec, /api/cli/exec) that can't use --from-json. The merge runs server-side and the target term must already exist (404 otherwise). Deploy-gated: against an un-updated backend these flags no-op (the value is preserved, not corrupted).
  - An append flag COMPOSES with plain overwrite flags for OTHER fields in the same call: \`--definition "new" --add-synonyms "x"\` overwrites the definition AND merges the synonym in one request. Only the same-field twin is rejected (exit 4): --definition⊥--append-definition and --synonyms⊥--add/remove-synonyms. Deploy-gated: an un-updated backend drops the plain field instead of composing — until it deploys, set OTHER fields in a separate call.

EXAMPLES
  ib glossary set valumassa --definition "Pumpattava betonimassa." --synonyms "massaa,valua" --related "ib keikka" --reason "groom"
  ib glossary set puomi --synonyms "boom,nollakone,puomiton" --reason "add synonyms only"
  ib glossary set pumppari --definition "Updated def." --update-only --reason "groom"
  ib glossary set loma --from-json loma.json --reason "groom"
  ib glossary set puomi --add-synonyms "nollakone" --reason "add one synonym"
  ib glossary set tilaus --append-definition "Convention: UI says tilaus, code says keikka." --reason "append clause"
"
`;

