  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

SEE ALSO
  ib legal show, ib legal status

EXAMPLES
  ib legal types
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib legal versions matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib legal versions <typeName> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  All versions of a document type, newest first. Every row carries a lifecycle status: draft (saved, never published) | active (live now, also isActive=1) | archived (superseded former-active) | deleted (soft-deleted). Use --status to filter. Content stripped; fetch one version with ib legal get, or compare two with ib legal diff.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <typeName> STRING    Document type name (see ib legal types) (required)

FLAGS
  --owner NUMBER    Filter by ownerAsiakasId tenant scope
  --status STRING    Filter by lifecycle status: draft|active|archived|deleted

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{documentId, version, title, status, isActive, effectiveDate, createdBy, createdTime, notes, ownerAsiakasId}>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

SEE ALSO
  ib legal get, ib legal diff, ib legal drafts, ib legal activate

EXAMPLES
  ib legal versions TOS
  ib legal versions TOS --status draft
  ib legal versions BETONIJERRY_TOS
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib log by-entity-date matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib log by-entity-date [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Changes affecting deliveries DATED in the window — filters by the entity's own date (keikka.pumppuAika / grid_palkit.starttime), NOT the change timestamp. This is what the grid Muutoshistoria drawer shows: 'everything that touched that day's deliveries, whenever the change was made'. GET /api/changes/by-entity-date/:ownerAsiakasId. Admin only. NOTE: reason/impersonatedByPersonName are null until the 2026-06 aggregate-procs backend deploy.
  Permissions: requires isAnyAdmin (asiakasAdmin/laskuAdmin/system admin).
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

FLAGS
  --entity-type STRING    keikka or palkki (required)
  --from DATE    Entity-date window start (or today/yesterday/tomorrow) (required)
  --to DATE    Entity-date window end (or today/yesterday/tomorrow) (required)
  --owner NUMBER    ownerAsiakasId (default: active company)
  --limit NUMBER    Max rows kept client-side (cap 2000) (default: 200)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ changeId, entityType, entityId, field, oldValue, newValue, changeType, personName, at, description, keikkaTilaContext, deviceType, palkkiText, palkkiVehicleRegNo, reason, impersonatedByPersonName }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not an admin in the owner company → use an admin token
  exit 4  entityType not keikka|palkki, or bad dates (client-side) → use --entity-type keikka|palkki and ISO dates or today/yesterday/tomorrow
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

SEE ALSO
  ib log range

EXAMPLES
  ib log by-entity-date --entity-type keikka --from today --to today
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib log entity matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib log entity <entityType> <entityId> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Change-tracker audit trail for ONE entity of any type — who changed which field, when, old→new, and the --reason recorded by writes. GET /api/changes/:entityType/:entityId/:ownerAsiakasId; owner defaults to the active company. entityType is validated client-side against the offline catalog (\`ib log types\`); 'keikka' folds in the keikka's keikkaBetoni rows; deprecated 'kuski' is accepted with a stderr note. --field filters client-side.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <entityType> STRING    One of \`ib log types\` (e.g. keikka, vehicle, pumppuRequest) (required)
  <entityId> NUMBER    The entity's id (see entityIdMeaning in \`ib log types\`) (required)

FLAGS
  --owner NUMBER    ownerAsiakasId (default: active company)
  --limit NUMBER    Max rows (capped at 500) (default: 100)
  --field STRING    Filter by changeTracker fieldName (client-side)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ changeId, entityType, entityId, field, oldValue, newValue, changeType, personId, personName, at, description, reason, impersonatedByPersonName, keikkaTilaContext, deviceType }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not a member of that company — or entityType personAvailability without an admin role → ib company switch to that owner, or use an admin token
  exit 4  Unknown entityType (client-side validation) → ib log types
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - personAvailability is admin-gated server-side; every other type needs company membership only.
  - Shortcuts: ib keikka|vehicle|worksite log (same row shape) and ib person|customer log (slimmer rows without entityType/entityId).

SEE ALSO
  ib log types, ib keikka log, ib log latest

EXAMPLES
  ib log entity keikka 12345
  ib log entity vehicle 53 --field kuskit
  ib log entity pumppuRequest 17
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib log latest matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib log latest [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Newest changes across the whole active company, optionally one entityType — admin view for 'what just happened'. GET /api/changes/latest/:ownerAsiakasId. NOTE: reason/impersonator columns appear only after the 2026-06 aggregate-procs backend deploy; until then they are null.
  Permissions: requires isAnyAdmin (asiakasAdmin/laskuAdmin/system admin).

FLAGS
  --entity-type STRING    Filter to one entityType
  --owner NUMBER    ownerAsiakasId (default: active company)
  --limit NUMBER    Max rows (server cap 500) (default: 100)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ changeId, entityType, entityId, field, oldValue, newValue, changeType, personId, personName, at, description, reason, impersonatedByPersonName, keikkaTilaContext, deviceType }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not an admin in the owner company → use an admin token, or per-entity \`ib log entity\`
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

SEE ALSO
  ib log range, ib log by-entity-date

EXAMPLES
  ib log latest
  ib log latest --entity-type keikka --limit 50
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib log range matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib log range [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  All changes MADE within a time window (by change timestamp), optional entityType/person filters — admin forensic view. GET /api/changes/range/:ownerAsiakasId. The backend has no row cap; --limit slices client-side (truncated:true when cut). NOTE: reason/impersonatedByPersonName are null until the 2026-06 aggregate-procs backend deploy.
  Permissions: requires isAnyAdmin (asiakasAdmin/laskuAdmin/system admin).
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

FLAGS
  --from DATE    Window start, YYYY-MM-DD or ISO datetime (or today/yesterday/tomorrow) (required)
  --to DATE    Window end, YYYY-MM-DD or ISO datetime (or today/yesterday/tomorrow) (required)
  --entity-type STRING    Filter to one entityType
  --person NUMBER    Filter to one actor personId
  --owner NUMBER    ownerAsiakasId (default: active company)
  --limit NUMBER    Max rows kept client-side (cap 2000) (default: 200)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ changeId, entityType, entityId, field, oldValue, newValue, changeType, personId, personName, at, description, reason, impersonatedByPersonName }> (+truncated when --limit cut rows)

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not an admin in the owner company → use an admin token
  exit 4  Invalid --from/--to (client-side) → use YYYY-MM-DD or ISO datetime; today/yesterday/tomorrow are also accepted
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Backend rejected the dates → use ISO date strings
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

SEE ALSO
  ib log by-entity-date

EXAMPLES
  ib log range --from 2026-06-01 --to 2026-06-10
  ib log range --from yesterday --to today --entity-type keikka --person 63
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib log types matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib log types [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Offline catalog of changeTracker entityTypes: what each entityId means, the server-side read gate, and notes (deprecated kuski, keikka⊃keikkaBetoni fold-in, pumppuRequest two-party rows). No network, no auth.
  Auth: none (public).

FLAGS
  (none)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ entityType, entityIdMeaning, gate: 'member'|'admin', notes, deprecated? }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 0  Always succeeds (offline static list) → n/a

EXAMPLES
  ib log types
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib log user matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib log user [<personId>] [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Changes MADE BY a person. Without personId: your own recent changes (GET /api/changes/user/recent/:owner — any member). With personId: that person's changes (GET /api/changes/user/:personId/:owner — self or admin). Rows carry entityDisplayName (e.g. '12345 - Tilaus') instead of personName (the actor IS the queried person).
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <personId> NUMBER    Whose changes (omit = yourself; others need admin) (optional)

FLAGS
  --owner NUMBER    ownerAsiakasId (default: active company)
  --limit NUMBER    Max rows (cap 500) (default: 100)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ changeId, entityType, entityId, field, oldValue, newValue, changeType, at, description, deviceType, entityDisplayName, reason, impersonatedByPersonName }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Another person's history without an admin role → omit personId, or use an admin token
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

EXAMPLES
  ib log user
  ib log user 63 --limit 50
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message board all matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message board all [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  List EVERY notice for the company including expired and not-yet-started ones (the admin-panel view). Requires an asiakas admin/editor or ilmoitustaulu editor.
  Permissions: requires auth.page.ilmoitustaulu.edit, auth.page.ilmoitustaulu.editOwn.

FLAGS
  (none)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ messageId, ownerAsiakasId, title, body, priority, startDate, expiresAt, createdAt, updatedAt, createdBy }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not an admin/editor (writes + \`all\`/\`get\` require it) → an asiakas admin/editor or ilmoitustaulu editor must run it
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Validation error (missing title/text/start-date, bad priority/date) → check the flags
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

SEE ALSO
  ib message board list

EXAMPLES
  ib message board all
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message board create matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message board create [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Create a notice (POST). --title, --text and --start-date are required; --priority defaults to info; --expires-at is optional (omit = never expires). Requires admin/editor. --reason required.
  Permissions: requires auth.page.ilmoitustaulu.edit, auth.page.ilmoitustaulu.editOwn.
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

FLAGS
  --title STRING    Notice title (required)
  --text STRING    Notice body text (stored as body) (required)
  --priority STRING    info | warning | urgent (default info)
  --start-date DATE    Day the notice becomes visible: today | YYYY-MM-DD (required)
  --expires-at DATE    Last day visible: YYYY-MM-DD (omit = never expires)

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { messageId, ownerAsiakasId, title, body, priority, startDate, expiresAt, createdAt, updatedAt, createdBy } · { dryRun: true, proposed: {...} } on --dry-run

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not an admin/editor (writes + \`all\`/\`get\` require it) → an asiakas admin/editor or ilmoitustaulu editor must run it
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Validation error (missing title/text/start-date, bad priority/date) → check the flags
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - --dry-run previews the payload CLIENT-SIDE without writing (the route has no X-Dry-Run guard).

SEE ALSO
  ib message board update, ib message board delete

EXAMPLES
  ib message board create --title "Asema kiinni" --text "Perjantaina suljettu" --start-date today --priority warning --reason "tiedote"
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message board delete matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message board delete <messageId> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Delete a notice (DELETE, 204). Admins delete any row; editors only their own. --reason required.
  Permissions: requires auth.page.ilmoitustaulu.edit, auth.page.ilmoitustaulu.editOwn.

ARGUMENTS
  <messageId> NUMBER    Notice to delete (required)

FLAGS
  (none)

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  204 no content · { dryRun: true, messageId, wouldDelete: {...} } on --dry-run

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  No notice with that id for the company → ib message board all
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not an admin/editor (writes + \`all\`/\`get\` require it) → an asiakas admin/editor or ilmoitustaulu editor must run it
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Validation error (missing title/text/start-date, bad priority/date) → check the flags
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - --dry-run previews what would be deleted CLIENT-SIDE without writing.

EXAMPLES
  ib message board delete 7 --reason "vanhentunut"
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message board get matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message board get <messageId> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Get one notice by id. There is no single-message GET route, so it is resolved CLIENT-SIDE over \`all\` — and therefore needs the same admin/editor access. Unknown id → exit 5.
  Permissions: requires auth.page.ilmoitustaulu.edit, auth.page.ilmoitustaulu.editOwn.

ARGUMENTS
  <messageId> NUMBER    Notice to fetch (required)

FLAGS
  (none)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { messageId, ownerAsiakasId, title, body, priority, startDate, expiresAt, createdAt, updatedAt, createdBy }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  No notice with that id for the company → ib message board all
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not an admin/editor (writes + \`all\`/\`get\` require it) → an asiakas admin/editor or ilmoitustaulu editor must run it
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Validation error (missing title/text/start-date, bad priority/date) → check the flags
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

EXAMPLES
  ib message board get 7
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message board list matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message board list [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  List notices ACTIVE on a day (startDate ≤ day ≤ expiresAt, or no expiry), newest first. Open to any company member. --date takes today/yesterday/tomorrow or YYYYMMDD (defaults to today). The web UI's per-device dismiss state is NOT applied — the CLI returns the full active set.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

FLAGS
  --date DATE    Day to query: today | yesterday | tomorrow | YYYYMMDD (default today)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ messageId, ownerAsiakasId, title, body, priority, startDate, expiresAt, createdAt, updatedAt, createdBy }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not an admin/editor (writes + \`all\`/\`get\` require it) → an asiakas admin/editor or ilmoitustaulu editor must run it
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Validation error (missing title/text/start-date, bad priority/date) → check the flags
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - Requires the ilmoitustaulu module enabled for the company.
  - The active-list endpoint uses compact YYYYMMDD (not ISO) — the CLI converts for you.

SEE ALSO
  ib message board all, ib message board get

EXAMPLES
  ib message board list
  ib message board list --date 20260614
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message board update matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message board update <messageId> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Update a notice (PUT). GET-merges the current row (over \`all\`) so omitted fields are preserved — the backend overwrites the whole row. Admins edit any row; editors only their own. --reason required.
  Permissions: requires auth.page.ilmoitustaulu.edit, auth.page.ilmoitustaulu.editOwn.
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

ARGUMENTS
  <messageId> NUMBER    Notice to update (required)

FLAGS
  --title STRING    Notice title
  --text STRING    Notice body text (stored as body)
  --priority STRING    info | warning | urgent
  --start-date DATE    Day the notice becomes visible: today | YYYY-MM-DD
  --expires-at DATE    Last day visible: YYYY-MM-DD (pass "" to clear the expiry)

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { messageId, ownerAsiakasId, title, body, priority, startDate, expiresAt, createdAt, updatedAt, createdBy } · { dryRun: true, messageId, current, proposed } on --dry-run

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  No notice with that id for the company → ib message board all
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not an admin/editor (writes + \`all\`/\`get\` require it) → an asiakas admin/editor or ilmoitustaulu editor must run it
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Validation error (missing title/text/start-date, bad priority/date) → check the flags
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - --dry-run previews the merged row CLIENT-SIDE without writing (no server X-Dry-Run guard).

SEE ALSO
  ib message board get

EXAMPLES
  ib message board update 7 --priority urgent --reason "nostettu kiireelliseksi"
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message chat delete matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message chat delete <messageId> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Soft-delete a chat message (DELETE /api/messages/threads/:id/messages/:messageId; sets isDeleted=1, so it vanishes from every read). The author may delete their OWN message only while it is unanswered (no later reply from another participant); a sysadmin/developer may moderate any message in a thread they can access. --dry-run previews CLIENT-SIDE.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <messageId> NUMBER    Message id to delete (the message PK) (required)

FLAGS
  --thread NUMBER    Thread id the message belongs to
  --tarjous NUMBER    Resolve the thread from this pumppuRequestId (one match required)

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { messageId, threadId, deleted:true } (+ alreadyDeleted:true if already gone) · { dryRun:true, threadId, wouldDelete:{ messageId, body, senderPersonId } } on --dry-run

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not the author (and not a developer) → you can only delete your own messages
  exit 4 (HTTP 409)  Already answered       → a message someone replied to after cannot be retracted — delete the newest first
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  Thread or message not found → check the threadId/messageId
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - Soft-delete: the row is kept for audit but is filtered from list/threads/unread (all carry isDeleted=0). There is no hard delete.
  - --dry-run only issues a GET (thread messages) to echo the target — it works under --read-only and never deletes (the route has no X-Dry-Run guard).
  - Locate the thread with --thread <id> or --tarjous <id>; a tarjous with multiple threads requires --thread.
  - Deploy-gated: the DELETE route must be deployed to the target backend before this works.

SEE ALSO
  ib message chat send, ib message chat list

EXAMPLES
  ib message chat delete 5 --thread 3 --reason "test cleanup"
  ib message chat delete 5 --tarjous 23 --dry-run
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message chat edit matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message chat edit <messageId> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Edit a chat message's body (PATCH /api/messages/threads/:id/messages/:messageId). Author-only and only while unanswered (no later reply from a different participant). Moderators cannot edit. Sets editedAt, emits message:edited, no-ops if the body is unchanged. --dry-run previews the from→to diff CLIENT-SIDE.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <messageId> NUMBER    Message id to edit (the message PK) (required)

FLAGS
  --thread NUMBER    Thread id the message belongs to
  --tarjous NUMBER    Resolve the thread from this pumppuRequestId
  --body STRING    New message text (max 4000 chars) (required)

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { messageId, threadId, senderPersonId, body, editedAt, ... } (enriched row) · { messageId, threadId, unchanged:true } on no-op · { dryRun:true, threadId, wouldEdit:{ messageId, from, to } } on --dry-run

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Empty / too-long body  → body is required, max 4000 chars
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not the author         → you can only edit your own messages
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  Thread or message not found → check the threadId/messageId
  exit 4 (HTTP 409)  Answered or deleted    → you cannot edit a message that was replied to, or a deleted one
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - Author-only — no moderator override (rewriting another person's words is worse than deleting).
  - --dry-run lists the thread to show the diff; it never PATCHes (works under --read-only).
  - Deploy-gated: the PATCH route must be deployed to the target backend.

SEE ALSO
  ib message chat send, ib message chat delete

EXAMPLES
  ib message chat edit 7 --thread 3 --body "korjattu teksti" --reason typo
  ib message chat edit 7 --tarjous 23 --body "korjattu" --dry-run
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message chat list matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message chat list [<threadId>] [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  List messages in a thread, oldest first. Does NOT mark the thread read (use \`ib message chat mark-read\`). Target by threadId or --tarjous; --since backfills, --limit caps.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <threadId> NUMBER    Thread id (omit when using --tarjous) (optional)

FLAGS
  --tarjous NUMBER    Resolve the thread from this pumppuRequestId
  --since STRING    Only messages created after this ISO timestamp
  --limit NUMBER    Max messages (server max 500) (default: 100)
  --deleted BOOLEAN    Include soft-deleted messages (your own; all for developers)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ messageId, threadId, senderPersonId, senderAsiakasId, kind, body, source, sourceNote, createdAt, editedAt, personFirstName, personLastName, senderAsiakasNimi }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not a participant of this thread → you can only read threads you are part of
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - Reading does NOT stamp lastReadAt — safe for an AI to browse without clearing your unread badge.
  - source/sourceNote are null until the provenance backend change is deployed.
  - --deleted sets ?includeDeleted=1: you see your own deleted rows, developers see all; rows carry isDeleted.

SEE ALSO
  ib message chat send, ib message chat mark-read

EXAMPLES
  ib message chat list 42
  ib message chat list --tarjous 23 --limit 20
  ib message chat list 42 --since 2026-06-14T10:00:00Z
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message chat mark-read matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message chat mark-read [<threadId>] [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Mark a thread read — stamp your lastReadAt to now (POST /api/messages/threads/:id/read), clearing the unread badge. A write, so blocked under --read-only.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <threadId> NUMBER    Thread id (omit when using --tarjous) (optional)

FLAGS
  --tarjous NUMBER    Resolve the thread from this pumppuRequestId

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { lastReadAt }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not a participant of this thread → you can only mark threads you are part of
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - Deliberately separate from \`list\` so reading never auto-marks (an AI can browse without clearing your unread state).

SEE ALSO
  ib message chat list, ib message chat threads

EXAMPLES
  ib message chat mark-read 42
  ib message chat mark-read --tarjous 23
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message chat restore matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message chat restore <messageId> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Restore a soft-deleted chat message (POST /api/messages/threads/:id/messages/:messageId/restore; isDeleted=0). The author OR a sysadmin/developer may restore. Idempotent (already-active → alreadyActive:true). Emits message:restored. Find deleted ids with \`ib message chat list --deleted\`. --dry-run previews CLIENT-SIDE via the deleted list.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <messageId> NUMBER    Message id to restore (the message PK) (required)

FLAGS
  --thread NUMBER    Thread id the message belongs to
  --tarjous NUMBER    Resolve the thread from this pumppuRequestId

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { messageId, threadId, restored:true } (+ alreadyActive:true if not deleted) · { dryRun:true, threadId, wouldRestore:{ messageId } } on --dry-run

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not the author (and not a developer) → you can only restore your own messages
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  Thread or message not found → check the threadId/messageId
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - Deleted messages are hidden from the normal list — use \`ib message chat list --deleted\` to find ids.
  - --dry-run lists deleted messages to confirm the target; it never restores (works under --read-only).
  - Deploy-gated: the restore route must be deployed to the target backend.

SEE ALSO
  ib message chat delete, ib message chat list

EXAMPLES
  ib message chat restore 7 --thread 3 --reason "deleted by mistake"
  ib message chat restore 7 --tarjous 23 --dry-run
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message chat search matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message chat search <query> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Search your own chat messages by body text (GET /api/messages/search). Scoped to threads you participate in (the participant JOIN is the tenant boundary); non-deleted only; newest first. q min 2 chars; --limit default 50, max 200.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <query> STRING    Body substring to search for (min 2 chars) (required)

FLAGS
  --limit NUMBER    Max results (server max 200) (default: 50)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ messageId, threadId, contextType, contextId, senderPersonId, body, createdAt, personFirstName, personLastName }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Query too short        → q must be at least 2 characters
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - Only your own threads are searched — the participant JOIN is the tenant boundary.
  - Substring (LIKE) match; literal % / _ in the query are matched literally.
  - Deploy-gated: the /search route must be deployed to the target backend.

SEE ALSO
  ib message chat list, ib message chat threads

EXAMPLES
  ib message chat search "betoni"
  ib message chat search "ajoyhteys" --limit 20
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message chat send matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message chat send [<threadId>] [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Send a message to a thread (POST /api/messages/threads/:id/messages). Outward-facing: the recipient sees it and gets a push. --dry-run previews the body + recipients CLIENT-SIDE without sending. --reason is stored as the message's sourceNote (optional).
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <threadId> NUMBER    Thread id (omit when using --tarjous) (optional)

FLAGS
  --tarjous NUMBER    Resolve the thread from this pumppuRequestId
  --body STRING    Message text (max 4000 chars) (required)
  --source STRING    Provenance: web|cli|ai (default: IB_SOURCE env or cli)

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { messageId, threadId, senderPersonId, senderAsiakasId, kind, body, source, sourceNote, createdAt } · { dryRun:true, threadId, wouldSend:{ body, source, sourceNote, recipients:[{ personId, name, role }] } } on --dry-run

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Empty / too-long body  → body is required, max 4000 chars
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not a participant of this thread → you can only post to threads you are part of
  exit 4 (HTTP 409)  Thread archived        → archived threads are read-only
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - --dry-run only issues a GET (thread participants) — it works under --read-only and never persists.
  - --reason → sourceNote (optional; chat is conversational). source/sourceNote are persisted only after the provenance backend change deploys; until then the API silently ignores them.
  - An AI-driven send sets source=ai automatically via the IB_SOURCE env var.

SEE ALSO
  ib message chat list, ib message chat thread

EXAMPLES
  ib message chat send 42 --body "Onko tyomaalle ajoyhteys raskaalle kalustolle?"
  ib message chat send --tarjous 23 --body "Kiitos tarjouksesta" --dry-run
  ib message chat send 42 --body "Vahvistettu" --reason "confirmed by phone"
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message chat thread matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message chat thread [<threadId>] [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Get one thread's metadata + participants (display names, roles, asiakas). Target by threadId positional or resolve from --tarjous.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <threadId> NUMBER    Thread id (omit when using --tarjous) (optional)

FLAGS
  --tarjous NUMBER    Resolve the thread from this pumppuRequestId

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { thread: { threadId, contextType, contextId, ownerAsiakasId, createdAt, lastMessageAt, archivedAt }, participants: [{ participantId, personId, asiakasId, role, joinedAt, lastReadAt, leftAt, personFirstName, personLastName, asiakasNimi }] }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Not a participant of this thread → you can only read threads you are part of
  exit 5 (HTTP 404)  Thread not found       → verify the threadId / --tarjous
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - --tarjous resolves client-side over /threads/mine; if it matches multiple threads (one per competing provider) you get exit 4 listing the threadIds — pass one explicitly.

SEE ALSO
  ib message chat threads, ib message chat list

EXAMPLES
  ib message chat thread 42
  ib message chat thread --tarjous 23
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message chat threads matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message chat threads [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  List your conversational message threads (inbox), newest first, with unread counts and a last-message preview. Projects GET /api/messages/threads/mine into the list envelope; --unread / --tarjous filter client-side.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

FLAGS
  --unread BOOLEAN    Only threads with unreadCount > 0
  --tarjous NUMBER    Only threads for this pumppuRequestId

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ threadId, contextType, contextId, ownerAsiakasId, createdAt, lastMessageAt, lastReadAt, unreadCount, lastMessageBody }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - Only threads you participate in are returned (server-scoped by your personId).
  - A keikka thread (contextType 'keikka') appears here automatically once keikka messaging ships — no CLI change needed.

SEE ALSO
  ib message chat list, ib message chat thread

EXAMPLES
  ib message chat threads
  ib message chat threads --unread
  ib message chat threads --tarjous 23
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib message daily add matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib message daily add [<asiakasId>] [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Create a daily box for a company. With --init, calls /box/initialize for the caller's OWN company's first box (server derives the company + checks permission).
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

ARGUMENTS
  <asiakasId> NUMBER    Owner company (omit with --init) (optional)

FLAGS
  --asiakas NUMBER    Owner asiakasId (alias for the positional)
  --date DATE    Date the box is for (default 00000000 = undated default box)
  --title STRING    Box title
  --init BOOLEAN    Caller's own company's first box via /box/initialize (no asiakasId)

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { success, boxId?, created? }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Validation error (bad date/ids/missing fields) → check the flags
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

SEE ALSO
  ib message daily delete

EXAMPLES
  ib message daily add 8 --title "Tiedotteet"
  ib message daily add --init
"
`;

