exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib search matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib search <query> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Cross-entity unified search: customers, worksites, persons, vehicles, keikkas and sijainnit in ONE flat ranked list. Client-side parallel fan-out over the per-entity searches — use this to resolve "who/what is X" without guessing the entity type.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <query> STRING    Search string (required)

FLAGS
  --in STRING    Comma-separated subset of: customer,worksite,person,vehicle,keikka,sijainti
  --limit NUMBER    Max hits per entity (default: 5)
  --my-companies BOOLEAN    Search across every company you belong to (customer/worksite/person)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { items: [{ entity, id, label, detail, <nativeIdField> }], nextCursor: null, count, errors: [{ entity, message }] }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - A failing/denied entity degrades gracefully into errors[] — exit 0 if at least one entity succeeded; if ALL fail, exits with the first failure's mapped code.
  - Ordering: prefix label matches first, then entity order customer→worksite→person→vehicle→keikka→sijainti.
  - Each hit carries its native id field (asiakasId/tyomaaId/personId/vehicleId/keikkaId/sijaintiId) for a follow-up \`ib <entity> get <id>\`.
  - Sijainti is matched by name/address/typeName substring (type names like "jäteasema" match too) over scope=all — INCLUDING other companies' rows (supplier betoniasemat referenced by GPS visits/timeline). Newer backends pre-filter server-side; older ones return the own+shared 500-row scan and the filter runs client-side.
  - --my-companies covers customer/worksite/person only; vehicle and keikka stay scoped to the active company (sijainti is already scope=all).

EXAMPLES
  ib search kamppi
  ib search 0401234567 --in person,keikka
  ib search "Rudus" --in customer --limit 10
  ib search jäteasema --in sijainti
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib sijainti closest matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib sijainti closest [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Find the closest sijainti of a given sijaintiTypeId to a worksite (tyomaa), by straight-line distance. asiakasId defaults to the active company.
  Permissions: requires auth.page.sijainnit.read.

FLAGS
  --worksite NUMBER    Target tyomaaId (REQUIRED unless --tyomaa; same flag as the rest of the CLI)
  --tyomaa NUMBER    Target tyomaaId (Finnish alias of --worksite)
  --type NUMBER    sijaintiTypeId to search within (REQUIRED)
  --asiakas NUMBER    Owner asiakasId (defaults to active company)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { closestSijainti: {...}|null, closestDistance: number|null }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Invalid tyomaaId or missing coordinates → verify the worksite has lat/lng
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Permission denied      → check auth.page.sijainnit.read
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - No sijainti of the type → both fields null (the backend's 999999999 no-result sentinel distance is normalized to null).

EXAMPLES
  ib sijainti closest --worksite 555 --type 1
  ib sijainti closest --tyomaa 555 --type 1
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib sijainti create matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib sijainti create [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Create a new sijainti (POST /api/geocode/sijainti/add). REQUIRED: --name (sijaintiNimi) and --type (sijaintiTypeId). The CLI auto-fills the other NOT NULL columns the add proc needs: --lyh defaults to --name (truncated to 50 chars), --max-distance to 50, and --asiakas to your active company. Coordinates (--lat/--lng or --geocode) are persisted via a follow-up updateLatLng call (the add proc binds no lat/lng) and echoed as { lat, lng, coordsPersisted } so geocoding is verifiable without a re-read. Provide typed flags or --body JSON; typed flags win over --body.
  Permissions: requires auth.page.sijainnit.edit.

FLAGS
  --body JSON    JSON object with the new sijainti fields (optional if typed flags given)
  --name STRING    sijaintiNimi (REQUIRED)
  --address STRING    sijaintiOsoite1 (street)
  --type NUMBER    sijaintiTypeId (REQUIRED; see \`ib sijainti types\`)
  --lat NUMBER    Latitude (persisted via updateLatLng + echoed)
  --lng NUMBER    Longitude (persisted via updateLatLng + echoed)
  --lyh STRING    sijaintiLyh — short code/abbreviation, ≤50 chars (defaults to --name)
  --max-distance NUMBER    maxDeliveryDistance in km (default 50)
  --asiakas NUMBER    Owner asiakasId (defaults to your active company)
  --geocode BOOLEAN    Resolve lat/lng from the address via Google Maps when coordinates are not given (then persisted + echoed)

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { sijaintiId, success, lat?, lng?, coordsPersisted? } — lat/lng/coordsPersisted present when coordinates were given (coordsPersisted:false on --dry-run)

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Validation failed      → fix --body fields
  exit 4 (HTTP 400)  Address could not be geocoded (--geocode, status ZERO_RESULTS) → supply a fuller --address or pass --lat/--lng directly
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Permission denied      → check auth.page.sijainnit.edit
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

EXAMPLES
  ib sijainti create --name "Depot A" --type 1
  ib sijainti create --name "Depot A" --address "Industrial St 1, Helsinki" --type 1 --geocode
  ib sijainti create --name "Depot A" --address "Industrial St 1" --type 1 --lat 60.17 --lng 24.94 --lyh "DEP-A" --max-distance 80
  ib sijainti create --body '{"sijaintiNimi":"Depot A","sijaintiTypeId":1}'
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib sijainti dashboard matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib sijainti dashboard [<sijaintiId>] [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  One-shot Address Information Dashboard report for a sijainti (location) — merges weather, building, cadastral parcel, nearby traffic cameras, nearby sijainnit, worksite deliveries, and nearby vehicles into a single JSON, with each section independently degrading to forbidden/error instead of failing the whole report. Resolve the point from EXACTLY ONE of the positional sijaintiId or --address.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <sijaintiId> NUMBER    sijaintiId to report on (mutually exclusive with --address) (optional)

FLAGS
  --address STRING    Street address to resolve the point from, instead of sijaintiId (mutually exclusive)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --company ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { point:{lat,lng}|null, address:string|null, weather, building, parcel, cameras, sijainti, deliveries, vehicles } — each section is { status:'ok'|'empty'|'forbidden'|'error', data?, error? }; a forbidden/error section never fails the whole command

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 4  Missing or ambiguous point input → pass exactly one of <sijaintiId> or --address
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - Per-section gating mirrors the FE dashboard: weather/cameras/vehicles degrade to forbidden when the company module is off; building/parcel are open to any authenticated user; a bad address or unresolvable point degrades EVERY section to error instead of failing the command.
  - The \`sijainti\` section reports sijainnit found NEARBY the resolved point (~2 km) — unrelated to the sijaintiId positional used to resolve the point itself.
  - \`deliveries\` reports worksite (tyomaa) delivery volume near the point; \`vehicles\` reports nearby BetoniJerry ecofleet vehicles.

SEE ALSO
  ib worksite dashboard, ib opendata building, ib opendata parcel, ib sijainti list

EXAMPLES
  ib sijainti dashboard 42
  ib sijainti dashboard --address "Oraspolku 2, Helsinki"
"
`;

